## Task

Create `POST /api/projects/[id]/issues/[issueNumber]/comment` - An endpoint to add comments to GitHub issues.

## Why

The "Save Summary" feature needs a way to post conversation summaries as GitHub comments. This endpoint provides that capability.

## Implementation

```typescript
// src/app/api/projects/[id]/issues/[issueNumber]/comment/route.ts

import { exec } from "child_process"
import { promisify } from "util"
import { configService } from "@/lib/services/config"
import { NextResponse } from "next/server"

const execAsync = promisify(exec)

export async function POST(
  request: Request,
  { params }: { params: Promise<{ id: string; issueNumber: string }> }
) {
  const { id, issueNumber } = await params
  const { body } = await request.json()

  if (!body || typeof body !== "string") {
    return NextResponse.json(
      { error: "Comment body is required" },
      { status: 400 }
    )
  }

  const project = await configService.getProject(id)
  if (!project) {
    return NextResponse.json(
      { error: "Project not found" },
      { status: 404 }
    )
  }

  try {
    // Use gh CLI to add comment
    // Escape the body for shell safety
    const escapedBody = body.replace(/"/g, "\\\"")

    await execAsync(
      `gh issue comment ${issueNumber} --body "${escapedBody}"`,
      { cwd: project.path }
    )

    return NextResponse.json({ success: true }, { status: 201 })
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Failed to post comment:", error)
    return NextResponse.json(
      { error: "Failed to post comment to GitHub" },
      { status: 500 }
    )
  }
}
```

## Shell Escaping Consideration

The comment body might contain:
- Quotes
- Backticks  
- Newlines
- Special characters

A safer approach might use stdin:
```bash
echo "$body" | gh issue comment 42 --body-file -
```

Or write to temp file first.

