## Implementation Notes

### Auto-initialization
```typescript
async getConfig(): Promise<MaestroConfig> {
  const configPath = path.join(os.homedir(), ".maestro", "config.json");
  try {
    const content = await fs.readFile(configPath, "utf-8");
    return JSON.parse(content);
  } catch (err) {
    if (err.code === "ENOENT") {
      const defaultConfig = { projects: [] };
      await this.saveConfig(defaultConfig);
      return defaultConfig;
    }
    throw err;
  }
}
```

### Directory Creation
```typescript
async saveConfig(config: MaestroConfig): Promise<void> {
  const dir = path.join(os.homedir(), ".maestro");
  await fs.mkdir(dir, { recursive: true });
  await fs.writeFile(
    path.join(dir, "config.json"),
    JSON.stringify(config, null, 2)
  );
}
```

### UUID Generation
Use `crypto.randomUUID()` (built into Node.js).

### Symlink Resolution
**IMPORTANT**: Resolve symlinks BEFORE storing paths to avoid issues when symlinks change:
```typescript
async addProject(inputPath: string, name?: string): Promise<ProjectConfig> {
  // Resolve symlinks to get the real path
  const realPath = await fs.realpath(inputPath);
  // Then validate and store realPath
}
```

### Path Utilities
```typescript
toDisplayPath(absolutePath: string): string {
  const home = this.getHomeDir();
  if (absolutePath.startsWith(home)) {
    return "~" + absolutePath.slice(home.length);
  }
  return absolutePath;
}

toAbsolutePath(displayPath: string): string {
  if (displayPath.startsWith("~/") || displayPath === "~") {
    return path.join(this.getHomeDir(), displayPath.slice(1));
  }
  return displayPath;
}

isWithinHome(testPath: string): boolean {
  const resolved = path.resolve(testPath);
  const home = this.getHomeDir();
  // Handle both with and without trailing separator
  return resolved === home || resolved.startsWith(home + path.sep);
}

getParentPath(filePath: string): string | null {
  const parent = path.dirname(filePath);
  // Stop at home directory
  if (!this.isWithinHome(parent) || parent === filePath) {
    return null;
  }
  return parent;
}
```

## Error Handling
Define specific error types for clear API responses:
```typescript
export class ConfigError extends Error {
  constructor(
    message: string,
    public code: "ENOENT" | "EACCES" | "PARSE_ERROR" | "VALIDATION"
  ) {
    super(message);
    this.name = "ConfigError";
  }
}
```

## Edge Cases
- **Corrupted JSON**: Throw ConfigError with code "PARSE_ERROR", let API layer handle
- **Permission denied**: Throw ConfigError with code "EACCES", user needs to fix permissions
- **Concurrent writes**: Last write wins (acceptable for v1, single user)
- **Symlinks in path**: Resolve with `fs.realpath()` before storing

