## Task

Create a type adapter that converts our current `ChatMessage` interface to the format AI Elements expects.

## Why

AI Elements components use a `parts` array structure for messages, while our current implementation uses a flat `content` string. We need an adapter layer to bridge this gap without changing our backend.

## Current Message Type

```typescript
interface ChatMessage {
  id: string;
  role: "user" | "assistant";
  content: string;
  timestamp: string;
}
```

## AI Elements Message Type

AI Elements expects messages with a `parts` array:
```typescript
interface AIMessage {
  id: string;
  role: "user" | "assistant";
  parts: MessagePart[];
}

type MessagePart = 
  | { type: "text"; text: string }
  | { type: "reasoning"; text: string }
  | { type: "source-url"; url: string };
```

## Implementation

Create `src/lib/utils/message-adapter.ts`:

```typescript
import type { ChatMessage } from "@/app/project/[id]/issue/[issueNumber]/page";

export interface AIElementsMessage {
  id: string;
  role: "user" | "assistant";
  parts: Array<{ type: "text"; text: string }>;
}

export function toAIElementsMessage(msg: ChatMessage): AIElementsMessage {
  return {
    id: msg.id,
    role: msg.role,
    parts: [{ type: "text", text: msg.content }],
  };
}

export function toAIElementsMessages(messages: ChatMessage[]): AIElementsMessage[] {
  return messages.map(toAIElementsMessage);
}
```

## Future Extension Points

The adapter is designed to be extended when we add:
- Reasoning/thinking support (parse special markers in content)
- Source citations (extract URLs from content)
- Code blocks (parse markdown code fences)

