## Purpose
Implement the `PATCH /api/projects/[id]` endpoint for updating project name or relocating its path.

## Use Cases
1. **Rename**: User wants to change the display name
2. **Revert to derived name**: User sets name to null
3. **Relocate**: Project was moved on disk, user points Maestro to new location

## Request Schema
```typescript
interface UpdateProjectRequest {
  name?: string | null;  // New display name, null to use derived
  path?: string;         // New path (for relocation)
}
```

At least one field must be provided.

## Response Schema
Returns the updated project (same shape as GET response item).

## Error Responses
| Status | Condition | Response |
|--------|-----------|----------|
| 400 | No fields to update | `{ error: "No fields to update" }` |
| 400 | Invalid path (if provided) | `{ error: "Path is not a directory" }` |
| 403 | Path outside home (if provided) | `{ error: "Path must be within home directory" }` |
| 404 | Project ID not found | `{ error: "Project not found" }` |
| 404 | New path doesn't exist | `{ error: "Path does not exist" }` |
| 409 | New path already tracked | `{ error: "A project with this path already exists" }` |

## Implementation
```typescript
// src/app/api/projects/[id]/route.ts
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";
import { configService } from "@/lib/services/config";
import fs from "fs/promises";

export async function PATCH(
  request: Request,
  { params }: { params: { id: string } }
) {
  try {
    const { id } = params;
    const body = await request.json();
    const { name, path: newPath } = body;

    // Check project exists
    const project = await configService.getProject(id);
    if (!project) {
      return NextResponse.json(
        { error: "Project not found" },
        { status: 404 }
      );
    }

    // Build updates
    const updates: Partial<ProjectConfig> = {};

    // Handle name update
    if ("name" in body) {
      // Explicit null or empty string → null (use derived)
      updates.name = name?.trim() || null;
    }

    // Handle path update (relocation)
    if (newPath) {
      const absolutePath = configService.toAbsolutePath(newPath.trim());

      if (!configService.isWithinHome(absolutePath)) {
        return NextResponse.json(
          { error: "Path must be within home directory" },
          { status: 403 }
        );
      }

      try {
        await fs.access(absolutePath);
      } catch {
        return NextResponse.json(
          { error: "Path does not exist" },
          { status: 404 }
        );
      }

      const stat = await fs.stat(absolutePath);
      if (!stat.isDirectory()) {
        return NextResponse.json(
          { error: "Path is not a directory" },
          { status: 400 }
        );
      }

      // Check not duplicate (unless it's the same project)
      const existing = await configService.getProjects();
      const duplicate = existing.find(p => p.path === absolutePath && p.id !== id);
      if (duplicate) {
        return NextResponse.json(
          { error: "A project with this path already exists" },
          { status: 409 }
        );
      }

      updates.path = absolutePath;
    }

    if (Object.keys(updates).length === 0) {
      return NextResponse.json(
        { error: "No fields to update" },
        { status: 400 }
      );
    }

    const updated = await configService.updateProject(id, updates);

    return NextResponse.json({
      id: updated.id,
      path: updated.path,
      displayPath: configService.toDisplayPath(updated.path),
      name: updated.name,
      displayName: updated.name ?? configService.deriveDisplayName(updated.path),
      addedAt: updated.addedAt,
      status: "active",
    });

  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Failed to update project:", error);
    return NextResponse.json(
      { error: "Failed to update project" },
      { status: 500 }
    );
  }
}
```

## Relocation Workflow
When a project goes missing:
1. User sees warning in UI
2. User clicks "Relocate"
3. Folder browser opens (ideally at parent of old path if it exists, else ~/dev)
4. User selects new location
5. PATCH request with new path
6. Project is now tracked at new location with same ID

The ID stays constant, preserving any bookmarks or links to `/project/[id]`.

